modules.description: This module implements a 2D mesh generator and Delaunay triangulator based on the Triangle library. It provides operations to create and manipulate planar straight-line graphs (PSLGs), generate triangulations with customizable constraints (like minimum angle, maximum area, and Steiner points), and compute Voronoi diagrams. It works with point sets, segments, and triangle meshes, supporting refinement, sub-mesh extraction, and point/triangle permutations, making it suitable for finite element analysis and geometric modeling.
